'''名譽上校'''或'''榮譽上校'''（{{lang-en|Colonel-in-Chief}}）在[[英聯邦國家|英聯邦國家]]軍隊是指一個軍團的{{tsl|en|Patronage|守護人}}，傳統上是由皇室成員來擔任。<ref>{{cite web|title=Colonel-in-Chief|url=http://www.royalanglianmuseum.org.uk/colonel-in-chief.html|publisher=The Royal Anglian Museum|accessdate=2015-01-18|quote=On joining, all members of the British Army swear an oath of allegiance to the ruling Sovereign, as by tradition the loyalty of the Army is to the Monarch and not the State. It is also '''traditional to have a member of the Royal Family as the honorary head, or Colonel-in-Chief, of the Regiment.'''|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150118123534/http://www.royalanglianmuseum.org.uk/colonel-in-chief.html|archive-date=2015-01-18|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 名譽上校不需要像正式的上校一樣負責團內的職務，但是他有必要瞭解團內正在進行的重要活動，並不定時到團內巡視，維持軍隊與皇室之間的聯繫。目前的[[英國陸軍|英國陸軍]]，有兩位外國君主在英國的團內擔任這個職位：
* [[約旦國王|約旦國王]]－[[輕龍騎兵團|輕龍騎兵團]]<ref>{{cite news|author=Richard Eden|title=Kate Middleton provokes battle between Army regiments|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/theroyalfamily/8544130/Kate-Middleton-provokes-battle-between-Army-regiments.html|date=2011-05-29|publisher=The Telegraph|accessdate=2015-01-18|archive-date=2019-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190628004702/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/theroyalfamily/8544130/Kate-Middleton-provokes-battle-between-Army-regiments.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
* [[丹麥女王|丹麥女王]]－{{tsl|en|Princess of Wales's Royal Regiment|威爾斯親王皇家團|威爾斯親王皇家團（女王親轄與王室漢普郡）}}<ref>{{cite web|title=THE PRINCESS OF WALES'S ROYAL REGIMENT (QUEEN'S AND ROYAL HAMPSHIRES)|url=http://www.queensroyalsurreys.org.uk/1661to1966/pwrr/pwrr.html|publisher=The Queen's Royal Surrey Regimental Association|accessdate=2015-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924083724/http://www.queensroyalsurreys.org.uk/1661to1966/pwrr/pwrr.html|archive-date=2015-09-24|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

這個職位雖然傳統上是由皇室成員來擔任，最終的選擇卻是由軍團本身來決定，例如{{tsl|en|Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry|帕特里夏公主加拿大輕步兵團}}的名譽上校應是由[[威靈頓公爵|威靈頓公爵]]擔任，軍團卻曾經邀請[[加拿大總督|加拿大總督]][[伍冰枝|伍冰枝]]成爲軍團的名譽上校。<ref>{{cite news |title=Clarkson to be given military honour |url=http://www.canada.com/edmontonjournal/news/local/story.html?id=44f65e8c-cc5c-42ec-b757-1374a99fd6d5&k=0 |author=Edmonton Journal |publisher=Canada.com |date=2007-02-04 |accessdate=2014-10-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080418232503/http://www.canada.com/edmontonjournal/news/local/story.html?id=44f65e8c-cc5c-42ec-b757-1374a99fd6d5&k=0 |archivedate=2008-04-18 }}</ref>

